race.comment: MACHINE MAN (6) is bursting to win and is sure to be well fancied. Has started just four times and has been runner-up last two, the latest beaten a length over the border. Looks hard to beat with any luck early from the wide draw. SIR AALI (8) was close to a win before a break and after a solid return was well off best last time at the provincials dropping right out on slow going. Regular rider back aboard here and off the low draw should take catching this line-up. WYNDSTAR (9) showed ability in first campaign for the Hayes yard and returns from a spell for a new barn on the back of two jump-outs. Trip suits fresh and could well be too strong for these. HASTA LA OINKERS (4) has had one run back from a break and was well held in sixth over 1430m at Naracoorte a week-and-a-half ago. Fitter and in the mix.
